{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"FileReaderSync.readAsArrayBuffer()","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FileReaderSync/readAsArrayBuffer","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/File_API\">File API</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FileReaderSync\"><code>FileReaderSync</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for File API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Blob\"><code>Blob</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/File\"><code>File</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FileList\"><code>FileList</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FileReader\"><code>FileReader</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/URL/createObjectURL\"><code>URL.createObjectURL()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/URL/revokeObjectURL\"><code>URL.revokeObjectURL()</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <code>readAsArrayBuffer()</code> method of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FileReaderSync\"><code>FileReaderSync</code></a> interface allows to read <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/File\"><code>File</code></a> or <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Blob\"><code>Blob</code></a> objects in a synchronous way into an <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/ArrayBuffer\"><code>ArrayBuffer</code></a>. This interface is <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Workers_API/Functions_and_classes_available_to_workers\">only available</a> in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Worker\">workers</a> as it enables synchronous I/O that could potentially block.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js-nolint notranslate\">readAsArrayBuffer(blob)\n</pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"blob\"><code>blob</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/File\"><code>File</code></a> or <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Blob\"><code>Blob</code></a> to read into the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/File\"><code>File</code></a> or <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/ArrayBuffer\"><code>ArrayBuffer</code></a>.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>An <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/ArrayBuffer\"><code>ArrayBuffer</code></a> representing the file's data.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"exceptions","title":"Exceptions","isH3":false,"content":"<p>The following exceptions can be raised by this method:</p>\n<dl>\n  <dt id=\"notfounderror\"><code>NotFoundError</code> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMException\"><code>DOMException</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Thrown if the resource represented by the DOM <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/File\"><code>File</code></a> or <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Blob\"><code>Blob</code></a> cannot be found, e.g. because it has been erased.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"securityerror\"><code>SecurityError</code> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMException\"><code>DOMException</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Thrown if one of the following problematic situation is detected:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>the resource has been modified by a third party;</li>\n      <li>too many read are performed simultaneously;</li>\n      <li>the file pointed by the resource is unsafe for a use from the Web (like it is a system file).</li>\n    </ul>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"notreadableerror\"><code>NotReadableError</code> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMException\"><code>DOMException</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Thrown if the resource cannot be read due to a permission problem, like a concurrent lock.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"encodingerror\"><code>EncodingError</code> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMException\"><code>DOMException</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Thrown if the resource is a data URL and exceed the limit length defined by each browser.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/FileAPI/#readAsArrayBufferSyncSection","title":"File API"}],"query":"api.FileReaderSync.readAsArrayBuffer"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.FileReaderSync.readAsArrayBuffer","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FileReaderSync/readAsArrayBuffer/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/API/File_API\" class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"This is a link to an unwritten page\">File API</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/File\"><code>File</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FileReaderSync\"><code>FileReaderSync</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FileReader\"><code>FileReader</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Blob\"><code>Blob</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Exceptions","id":"exceptions"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The readAsArrayBuffer() method of the FileReaderSync interface allows to read File or Blob objects in a synchronous way into an ArrayBuffer. This interface is only available in workers as it enables synchronous I/O that could potentially block.","popularity":0.0002,"modified":"2022-09-22T08:57:12.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"FileReaderSync.readAsArrayBuffer()","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/filereadersync/readasarraybuffer","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/filereadersync/readasarraybuffer/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/9568a168018a82b2a945227bac88ab70aba72f0e","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FileReaderSync","title":"FileReaderSync"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FileReaderSync/readAsArrayBuffer","title":"FileReaderSync.readAsArrayBuffer()"}],"pageTitle":"FileReaderSync.readAsArrayBuffer() - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}